gui_group_hinst(25.10)                                  gui_group_hinst(25.10)

Name
       gui_group_hinst  -  Moves  one level up the hierarchy for the specified
       module guide and displays the next module

Syntax
       gui_group_hinst

       [-help]

       [-type {flex_model} | <hname>]

       Moves one level up the hierarchy for the  specified  module  guide  and
       displays  the next module. The gui_group_hinst command is equivalent to
       the Group widget  on the toolbar.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each gui_group_hinst parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man gui_group_hinst

       <hname>
              Specifies the name of the hierarchical instance to be grouped.

       -type {<flex_model>}
              Specifies the type of objects to be grouped.  At  present,  only
              the flex_model type is supported.

Examples
              * The following command goes one level up the specified module:

                gui_group_hinst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST

              * The   following   command  groups  all  flexModels,  including
                flex_module and flex_instgroup, up to  the  partition  or  in-
                stance group level.

                gui_group_hinst -type flex_model

